eems not to have gone well. I tried to put a little of everything into a &quot;Hero&quot; class.<br>
<br>
Race/sign/focus: Breton/Steed/Fighter<br>
Primary Atts: Willpower/Endurance<br>
Majors: Spear, Heavy Armor, Destruction, Marksman, Illusion<br>
Minors: Stealth, Security, Restoration, Speechcraft, something else<br>
<br>
The idea was powerful, charismatic, resourceful.<br>
<br>
The reality: dog slow (even with Steed sign), too prone to taking melee damage (no block and marginal agility), helpless with the bow so far (intended to be a huge part of the character's approach). <br>
<br>
Of course I'm only level 2 so it's hard to tell. I was considering going all-out caster instead, but now I'm toying with a primary caster with monk attributes like hand to hand and either unarmored or light armor skill. Fast, quick, virtuous, and probably throw speechcraft in there too since I like being charismatic. <br>
<br>
Or maybe not.<br>
