<br>
Dark Elf Adventurer, birthsign: The Lady<br>
Focus: Combat<br>
Primary Stats: Strength, Agility<br>
Major Skills: Long Blade, Marksman, Stealth, Athletics, Medium Armor<br>
Minor Skills: Restoration, Security, Acrobatics, Alchemy, Light Armor<br>
<br>
The only skill that seems like a mistake was Light Armor, if I were to start over I'd probably take Speechcraft or Mysticism instead. Marksman does start out being really weak, but it picks up pretty quickly. With a steel longbow I can 2-hit most of the wildlife I'm fighting, like cliff racers or those big floating jellyfish thingies. I had to fight 3 bad guys at once last night, and managed to take out the mage in the back with 2 poison arrows before the 2 fighters reached me. I still miss a lot more than I hit though. <br>
<br>
Here's one tip I read that's really helped me work around my lack of Speechcraft. As soon as I could I joined the Mage Guild to get access to their spellmaker. Then I made a spell that boosts my personality by 40 points for 3 seconds - just long enough to cast it and initiate a conversation. It saves me a few bucks when dealing with merchants, but more importantly, it makes provoking Bad People into fights much easier. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
I'm starting to think this is a pretty big game. Huge, actually. I ran from Caldera to Gnar Mok last night, which look pretty close on the map, and it was a pretty good run. Just staying on the road, I passed a mine, a tomb, and a shipwreck off the coast that will need to be explored at some point. There's all kinds of tombs and ruins in the wilderness too. I'm betting you could play for weeks and still not see or do everything. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/ugharadin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gharadin</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_ball.gif" BORDER=0> at: 5/6/02 6:08:58 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#6B8E23><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub10.ezboard.com/ucreepypete.showPublicProfile?language=EN>CreepyPete</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#5F9EA0>(5/6/02 7:06:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub10.ezboard.com/fforgottentruthforeignlegiongeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1108.topic&index=12>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Morrowind</span><hr size=1> Stick with Marksman. I ran into a couple of bow wielding bastards last night that made me wish I'd went that way. Starting to think there is a positional damage system in game, sometimes the arrows are laughable, but other times they can do 25-30 I figure.<br>
<br>
If you have shortblade keep an eye out for a Dwemer Jinksword. 10 sec paralysis on it, but I tend to get flustered in combat and blow all of it's charges at once. I was under the impression that you had to recharge items once you blew the charges, but they regenerate naturally over time, so do NOT be hesitant to pick up some magic items. <br>
<br>
Hit level 14 or 15 last night, I forget. Still not 100 hps but I'm a good all rounder.<br>
<br>
Mysticism is SO nice once you get Mark and Recall. If the game world was small it wouldnt be so hot, but just knowing that if you can get IN somewhere getting out is gonna be cake makes it all worthwhile. =)  Or bind at a merchant and right before you gate out pick up a whole buncha heavy stuff.<br>
<br>
Great tip on that spell, gonna try that one tonight.<br>
<br>
Stealing: If you raise an alarm when you're stealing just get as far away as you can, drop the hot goods and run to go find a guard to pay your fine. They can't confiscate what you don't have on you. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
